comment_data.body: I can't reproduce running Flutter create on the command line and opening the project in IntelliJ? Can you provide more details on how you are created the Flutter project, which IDE you are using, and what version of Flutter and IntelliJ/AndroidStudio you are using?

Creating flutter project is fine but when I download a flutter project on Github for example and wanna open the project directory from Android Studio, this happens:

> In opening flutter project, always needed to Enable Dart and specify flutter location on Flutter SDK path in flutter setting.

Here is my `flutter doctor`:
```
[√] Flutter (Channel stable, v1.9.1+hotfix.5, on Microsoft Windows [Version 10.0.18362.418], locale fa-IR)

[√] Android toolchain - develop for Android devices (Android SDK version 29.0.0)
[√] Android Studio (version 3.5)
```

I'm not sure how much we can do to fix this given it is likely general IntelliJ behavior not something we really have control over.

Oh, that's ok but it's suffering.
You can close it if you want.
